<HEADLINE>
FT  29 APR 91 / International Company News: Air Canada Seeks To Cancel
Boeing Orders
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
AIR CANADA, caught by the international slump in air travel, has asked
Boeing to cancel orders and options on a long list of aircraft, writes
Robert Gibbens. The airline, privatised two years ago before the onset of
recession and the Gulf war, is asking Boeing to cancel orders on three
747-400s for first delivery in 1993 and is expected to seek cancellation of
orders for six 767-300s and options on another 12. Air Canada has been
losing money for several successive quarters and has to cut back on its
fleet renewal and expansion programme.
