gas and water cannon to block a protest march towards central Seoul on
Saturday afternoon.
A spokesman for the ruling Democratic Liberal Party said that the government
'whole-heartedly apologises to the nation'. He said that Mr Ahn Eung Mo,
home minister, would be superseded by Mr Lee Sang Yeon.
However, opposition groups said that the government's response, and the
issue of arrest warrants for the four policemen believed responsible, was
not enough.
