Act.
However, the Indian government is not showing concern over the decision,
although punishment and retaliation by the US against India's exports can be
taken after six months if Delhi makes no progress in protecting US
companies' intellectual property rights.
Dr Subramaniam Swamy, India's commerce minister, yesterday said 'we should
