India's exports to its largest trading partner, at a time when its
balance-of-payments position is critical, is in marked contrast with the
condemnation of the decision from Indian business and officials.
The subdued comment could also be related to India's hope that the US and
other donor countries will give emergency assistance to the country to help
tide it over its current payments problems.
