</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PHILIP COGGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Bank of Scotland is introducing an annual charge of Pounds 10 on its Classic
Visa and Mastercard credit cards. The charge will appear on statements
issued after July 5. The bank is softening the blow by reducing the interest
rate from 2.2 to 1.9 per cent a month, or 28.4 per cent a year. It is also
adding purchase protection insurance and two telephone helplines for home
and car owners.
